  "body": "The copy function in active_state messes up recent_block_hash field. The following happens when we call copy active state:\r\n\r\nSlot 1:\r\n- Before copy: [0,0,0,0,0xA]\r\n- After copy: [0xA,0xA,0xA,0xA,0xA] Should be [0,0,0,0,0xA]\r\n\r\nSlot 2:\r\n- Before copy:  [0xA,0xA,0xA,0xA,0xB]\r\n- After copy:  [0xB,0xB,0xB,0xB,0xB] Should be [0xA,0xA,0xA,0xA,0xB]\r\n\r\nSlot 3:\r\n- Before copy:  [0xB,0xB,0xB,0xB,0xC]\r\n- After copy:  [0xC,0xC,0xC,0xC,0xC] Should be [0xB,0xB,0xB,0xB,0xC]\r\n\r\n*Notice block hash for slot 0 (0xA) gets discarded during slot 3, which causes the block balance to be lower than usual. This is the reason why beacon node couldn't establish justified slot, justified streak and finalized slot. Therefore validator set changes don't happen and shuffling between validators don't happen. ",
